      "role": "user",
      "content": "Okay, I see. So the main outcome wasn't there. If I lead with the \"compelling subgroup data\" like you suggested, won't the board immediately dig into why the primary endpoint failed? It feels like we're trying to hide a setback. Be honest with me—if we present the data this way, are we actually giving them the full picture, or are we just trying to keep the funding alive by pivoting to the smaller wins?",
